The paper discusses automatic text summarisation in the field of software engineering, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. Additionally, the paper mentions the analysis of text properties and heuristics searches, which are common topics in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) categories. The use of machine learning techniques to generate human-like summaries also suggests a possible fit with the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Finally, the paper's focus on improving efficiency and enhancing quality aligns with the goals of the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category.
